<p>Browsing this automatically generated list can allow a precise understanding of what each application is doing (Figure C). If protection is enabled, TOMOYO Linux uses Mandatory Access Control to restrict each application to do only what the administrator has allowed it to do (Figure D). TOMOYO Linux can therefore be used as a system restriction tool, which can aid in:</p>
<ul>
<li>restricting services such as SSH and Apache</li>
<li>restricting system administrator operations</li>
<li>creating per-application networking firewalls</li>
<li>reducing damage caused by buffer overflows and other security exploits</li>
<li>deploying a honeypot system</li>
</ul>

